### Seed the swarm with a coding task
#
# Run create-session.http first. Paste the returned sessionId below.
# Then adjust `content` to describe the coding task. Send in order:
# createThread → seed message.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5555
@authKey = dev
@sessionId = PASTE_SESSION_ID_FROM_CREATE_SESSION

###
# 1. Create a shared thread with all three real agents as participants.

# @name createThread
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/puppet/default/{{sessionId}}/puppet/thread
Authorization: Bearer {{authKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "threadName": "coding task",
  "participantNames": ["planner", "implementer", "reviewer"]
}

###
# 2. Send the task into the thread, mentioning @planner first.
#    Edit `content` to describe your actual task. Keep it concrete —
#    the planner will decompose from there.

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/puppet/default/{{sessionId}}/puppet/thread/message
Authorization: Bearer {{authKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "threadId": "{{createThread.response.body.thread.id}}",
  "content": "Build a small CLI in Python that accepts a URL, fetches the page, extracts all hrefs from anchor tags, and prints them sorted and deduplicated. Include a pytest suite covering happy path + error cases (timeout, 404, malformed HTML). Use the requests + beautifulsoup4 libraries. @planner please start — decompose the task, decide file layout in /workspace, then hand to @implementer.",
  "mentions": ["planner"]
}
